Definition: an amendment to the Constitution of the United States that imposes restrictions on the government's prosecution of persons accused of crimes
Example: mandates due process of law and prohibits self-incrimination and double jeopardy; requires just compensation if private property is taken for public use
Synonyms: amendment, i, Bill_of_Rights, p, noun, group, law, c, an, to, the, Constitution, of, United, States, that, imposes, restrictions, on, government, s, prosecution, persons, accused, crimes, mandates, due, process, and, prohibits, self-incrimination, double, jeopardy, requires, just, compensation, if, private, property, is, taken, for, public, use
Category: noun.communication
